quot;suru&quot; are. As in, can I get some examples? <br>
<br>
 I know there's oodles for koto, like: &quot;Eigakan e iku koto ga arimasu&quot; or, &quot;Okaasan no ryoori o taberu koto ni shimasen&quot;.<br>
<br>
 As with suru, I'm not sure. I see the plain form of it used a lot in sentences (Kimi wo shiawase ni suru). Is there any stipulation on using shimasu and suru? Or would it be the same as tabemasu and taberu? What I'm getting at: Does it have any other uses than a verb? <br>
<br>
 EDIT: Another thing I was wondering about was the difference between &quot;Aru&quot; and &quot;Iru&quot;. Do you use &quot;Arimasu&quot; for living things and &quot;Imasu&quot; for inanimate things? <br>
<br>
 I guess I just get confused sometimes. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
 Thanks in advance...<br>
<br>
